+Name:           phpstan
+Version:        1.10.0
+Release:        0
+Summary:        PHP Static Analysis Tool
+License:        MIT
+URL:            https://github.com/phpstan/phpstan
+Source0:        https://github.com/phpstan/phpstan/archive/refs/tags/%{version}.tar.gz
+
+BuildArch:      noarch
+Requires:       php(x86-64) >= 7.2
+
+%description
+PHPStan is a static analysis tool for PHP that focuses on finding errors
+in your code without actually running it. It detects whole classes of
+errors even from just looking at the code, such as calling methods on
+wrong objects and accessing properties with the wrong visibility, using
+null where a more specific value is expected, and so on.
+
+PHPStan comes with several analysis levels to choose from. The higher
+the level, the more thorough the analysis is, and the more false
+positives you might encounter.
+
+%prep
+%autosetup -T -P -n phpstan-%{version}
+
+sed -i 's|__DIR__ . '\''/phpstan.phar'\''|%{_datadir}/phpstan/phpstan.phar|g' phpstan
+
+%build
+# No compilation needed - pre-built PHAR archive
+
+%install
+install -Dm 0755 phpstan.phar   %{buildroot}%{_datadir}/phpstan/phpstan.phar
+install -Dm 0755 phpstan        %{buildroot}%{_bindir}/phpstan
+%fdupes -s %{buildroot}%{_datadir}
+
+%check
+# Run a basic self-test to ensure the PHAR works
+php %{buildroot}%{_bindir}/phpstan --version > /dev/null 2>&1 || :
+
+%files
+%doc LICENSE
+%{_bindir}/phpstan
+%{_datadir}/phpstan/phpstan.phar
+
+%changelog
